## Reaction Time: Correct, Incorrect, and All Trials

```{r fig-rt-comparison, fig.cap="Mean reaction time at pre- and post-test by group, computed three ways: correct trials only (left), incorrect trials only (centre), and all trials regardless of accuracy (right). Free y-axes within each panel; note that incorrect-trial means are based on a small number of observations given high overall accuracy."}
knitr::include_graphics(file.path(FIG_DIR, "fig2_rt_comparison.png"))
```

Because overall accuracy is high, incorrect-trial RT estimates rest on a small number of observations per cell (see the `n incorrect` column in the table above) and should be interpreted with appropriate caution. All-trial RT closely tracks correct-trial RT in this dataset.

